<section>
    <div class="description">
        <p>
            Master the electrical characteristics, safety wiring specifications,
            and control methods for high-power loads of relay outputs.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="learning-points">
        <h2>ðŸ“š Learning Points</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>
                Relay Working Principle and Function: Introduce the structure
                and role of relays, and common types of controlled devices
                (lighting, pumps, solenoid valves, etc.)
            </li>
            <li>
                Relay Electrical Parameters: Differences and selection between
                maximum resistive load (e.g., AC220V 9A / DC30V 9A) and
                inductive load
            </li>
            <li>
                Relay Wiring Specifications: Demonstrate wiring methods for
                Normally Open (NO), Normally Closed (NC), and Common (COM)
                terminals, paying attention to high and low voltage separation
            </li>
            <li>
                High-power Equipment Control: Introduce how to achieve safe
                control of high-power loads (such as three-phase motors,
                high-power heating rods) through external AC contactors when
                relay capacity is insufficient
            </li>
            <li>
                AC Contactor Wiring: Demonstrate the wiring method of
                IOTAutoMate relays driving AC contactor coils
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>
